## Amplitude Analytics API Platform

Amplitude provides a comprehensive suite of REST APIs for analytics data ingestion, user management, and data retrieval across their analytics platform. The API ecosystem supports real-time event tracking, user behavior analysis, cohort management, and enterprise-grade data governance features.

## Product Architecture and Relationships

The Amplitude API platform consists of several interconnected components organized around core analytics workflows:

**Data Ingestion Layer:**
- **HTTP V2 API** (`/2/httpapi`) serves as the primary event ingestion endpoint for server-to-server tracking
- **Batch Event Upload API** handles bulk data uploads with 20MB payload limits and rate limiting (1000 events/second per device)
- **Attribution API** (`/attribution`) processes mobile advertising attribution events using advertising IDs (IDFA, ADID, etc.)

**User and Group Management:**
- **Identify API** (`/identify`) manages user property updates and Device ID to User ID mappings without generating events
- **Group Identify API** (`/groupidentify`) handles group-level properties for account-based analytics
- **User Mapping API** (`/usermap`) provides cross-project user aliasing through global user IDs

**Data Retrieval and Export:**
- **Export API** (`/api/2/export`) enables bulk event data extraction in zipped JSON format with 4GB limits
- **Dashboard REST API** provides structured access to analytics data including funnels, retention, and segmentation
- **User Profile API** (`profile-api.amplitude.com/v1/userprofile`) retrieves comprehensive user profiles including computed properties and recommendations

**Analytics Enhancement:**
- **Behavioral Cohorts API** (v3/v5) manages user cohorts with asynchronous S3-based download workflows
- **Lookup Table API** (v1/v3) augments event and user properties through CSV-based property mappings
- **Chart Annotations API** (`/api/2/annotations`) enables programmatic chart annotation management

## Key Nomenclature and Definitions

**Core Identifiers:**
- `amplitude_id`: Amplitude's internal user identifier
- `user_id`: Customer-defined user identifier
- `device_id`: Device-specific identifier for anonymous tracking
- `session_id`: Session tracking identifier
- `insert_id`: Event deduplication identifier

**Event Structure:**
- `event_type`: The name/category of the tracked event
- `event_properties`: Custom properties associated with specific events
- `user_properties`: Properties associated with users across sessions
- `group_properties`: Properties for group-level analytics (requires Accounts add-on)

**Property Operations:**
- `$set`, `$setOnce`, `$add`, `$append`, `$prepend`, `$unset`: Standard property manipulation operations
- `$preInsert`, `$postInsert`, `$remove`: Advanced list manipulation operations

**Attribution and Mobile:**
- `idfa` (iOS Identifier for Advertiser), `idfv` (iOS Identifier for Vendor)
- `adid` (Google Advertising ID), `android_app_set_id`
- 72-hour attribution window for campaign matching

**API Infrastructure:**
- `api2.amplitude.com`: Primary API endpoint (US)
- `api.eu.amplitude.com`: EU residency endpoint
- `data-api.amplitude.com`: Lookup table and taxonomy operations
- `profile-api.amplitude.com`: User profile retrieval

## Broader Product Ecosystem Integration

The API platform integrates with Amplitude's broader analytics ecosystem through several key mechanisms:

**Plan-Based Feature Access:**
- **Growth/Enterprise Plans**: Advanced cohort operations, taxonomy management, SCIM provisioning
- **Accounts Add-on**: Group-level analytics and identification
- **Portfolio Add-on**: Cross-project user mapping capabilities
- **Activation Plan**: User profile API and recommendation features

**Data Governance and Compliance:**
- **GDPR/CCPA Compliance**: User Privacy API with 30-day deletion scheduling
- **SCIM 2.0**: Enterprise user provisioning and group management
- **Taxonomy API**: Enterprise schema management with PII/sensitive data classifications

**Workflow Integration:**
- **Release Management**: Programmatic release tracking with chart annotations
- **Event Streaming**: Delivery metrics and monitoring for real-time data pipelines
- **Warehouse Integration**: CDC (Change Data Capture) considerations for data warehouse synchronization

## API Endpoints and Technical Specifications

**Primary Ingestion Endpoints:**
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/2/httpapi` - Event ingestion
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/batch` - Bulk event upload
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/attribution` - Attribution events
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/identify` - User property updates
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/groupidentify` - Group property updates

**Data Retrieval Endpoints:**
- `GET api2.amplitude.com/api/2/export` - Event data export
- `GET profile-api.amplitude.com/v1/userprofile` - User profile retrieval
- Various Dashboard REST API endpoints for analytics queries

**Management Endpoints:**
- `POST/GET api2.amplitude.com/api/2/annotations` - Chart annotations
- `POST api2.amplitude.com/api/2/release` - Release creation
- Cohort API endpoints for user segment management
- SCIM endpoints for user/group provisioning

**Authentication Methods:**
- HTTP Basic Authentication (most APIs)
- API Key authentication (event ingestion)
- Secret Key authentication (User Profile API)
- SCIM Key authentication (SCIM API)

**Rate Limiting and Constraints:**
- Standard rate limits: 1000 events/second per device, 500K events/day
- Payload limits: 20MB for batch uploads, 4GB for exports
- Cohort limits: 2 million users per cohort
- File upload limits: 100MB for lookup tables

The platform supports both real-time and batch processing workflows, with comprehensive error handling, throttling mechanisms, and enterprise-grade security features for large-scale analytics implementations.